  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study will evaluate the effcts of transcranial direct current stimulation (tDCS) in
      combination with locomotor training in patients with Parkinson's disease (PDD) and freezing
      of gait (FOG).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      A randomized, sham-controlled, crossover study with an intervening washout period of 1 week
      will be performed to evaluate the effect of tDCS in conjunction with locomotor training (LT)
      in patients with PD. Order of tDCS and sham-tDCS will be randomized across subjects. Subjects
      with PD and FOG, will be randomly assigned to Group 1 (tDCS+LT - washout - sham-tDCS+LT) or
      Group 2 (sham-tDCS+LT - washout - tDCS+LT), with each washout period lasting 1 week. During
      each intervention session, subjects will receive the assigned tDCS ~or~ a sham-tDCS
      stimulation concomitant with LT.

      Kinematic data will be obtained using 3D motion capture as the subject walks along a 10-meter
      path. We will use single pulse TMS to evaluate the excitability of lower leg motor cortex.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
